WEEK 6 REPORT – SPOILAGE ANALYSIS, PERFORMANCE SCORING & DASHBOARD PREPARATION
Objective

To evaluate supplier performance by incorporating spoilage impact, develop a comprehensive performance scoring model, and prepare structured datasets for dashboard visualization and decision-making.

Activities Performed
Day 19 – Spoilage Impact Analysis
Derived spoilage metrics using defect rates and procurement quantities
Estimated financial loss due to spoilage for each supplier
Analyzed relationship between cost, defect rate, and spoilage
Identified high-loss suppliers contributing significantly to spoilage cost
Generated distribution and correlation visualizations for spoilage patterns

Day 20 – Supplier Performance Evaluation
Developed a composite performance scoring model combining reliability, risk, and spoilage factors
Ranked suppliers based on performance scores to identify top and low performers
Categorized suppliers into performance segments such as Top Performer, Stable Supplier, Needs Improvement, and Critical Risk
Designed a business decision framework for procurement actions
Generated KPI summary including total suppliers, top performers, and critical suppliers

Day 21 – Power BI Data Preparation
Structured final dataset for dashboard consumption by selecting key analytical features
Created multiple supporting datasets including KPI cards, category distribution, and top/bottom vendor lists
Prepared scatter plot and decision summary datasets for visualization
Ensured data was clean, consistent, and ready for direct integration into Power BI

Day 22 – Final Validation & Dashboard Logic
Validated dataset for missing values, duplicates, and data type consistency
Performed sanity checks on key metrics such as cost, defect rate, and performance score
Verified KPI calculations and supplier categorizations
Finalized a dashboard structure including KPI cards, category distributions, and performance visualizations
Generated a validated dataset for final dashboard implementation

Results
Spoilage impact was successfully quantified and linked to supplier performance
A multi-factor performance scoring system was developed for supplier evaluation
High-risk and low-performing suppliers were clearly identified
Clean and structured datasets were prepared for Power BI dashboard development
Data validation ensured reliability and accuracy of analytical outputs

Conclusion

Week 6 transformed the project from analytical exploration to decision-driven evaluation by integrating spoilage impact into supplier performance assessment. The development of a comprehensive scoring model and dashboard-ready datasets enabled clear identification of supplier risks and optimization opportunities, forming a strong foundation for business intelligence reporting.